'''Kemonomimi''' (獣耳 ''animal ears'') is an [[anime]] and [[manga]] terminology that describes humanoid characters that possess animal like features. The characters will be predominately human and any real animal characteristics are minimal, unlike [[kemono]] characters who possess a large percentage of animal parts in ratio with their human parts. Generally kemonomimi characters have ears and a tail which is animal like. Often this is just part of their attire and can be removed at will.

The term is used both in Japan and in some western subcultures, the term is used on the TAOchan/idlechan [[imageboard]] [http://www.teamtao.com/kemonomimi/wakaba.html] for example.

